CEPHALOTHORAX: Carapace oval, light yellow, shiny, finely reticulate; suffused with dark gray along margin and radiating lines; trident mark present; fovea present. Eyes, all rounded and equal in size. Sternum smooth, light yellow suffused with dark gray, as long as wide. Clypeus height 2 . Chelicerae light yellow, excavated; ~ 3 seta-tipped tubercles, last one very large (
